INTERSHOP IOM 4.5.0-SNAPSHOT Database Model   (revision 74152228c82611ddea9109abcbde8f916a191c6f)

Table oms.SupplierDO

List of all suppliers and their basic configuration.

Columns 

References[1] Column Type Constraints[2] Default Comment
id bigint PK, UNIQUE, NOT_NULL  
active boolean Whether the supplier is active or not. 
contentSupplier boolean NOT_NULL Whether the supplier is a content provider for product data.
Recommended to be FALSE. 
CountryCodeDefDO countryCodeDefRef integer NOT_NULL Could be used to determine which kind of country code the suppier is using in its APIs. 
CountryDefDO countryDefRef integer NOT_NULL The country where the supplier is located at. 
cutOffTime varchar(10) NOT_NULL Specifies the time by which an order must be submitted to the supplier to guarantee the minimum delivery time.
If the cutoff time already passed when the DOSE process for an order takes place, the planned delivery date is increased by one day.
Syntax: hh:mm (24-hour time format). Example 14:10 
deliveringSupplier boolean Whether the supplier delivers goods.
If FALSE, the supplier is not considered in the order assignment for a shop (DOSE process). 
legal boolean NOT_NULL Whether the supplier is a concrete supplier, or is used only for configuration purposes.
Recommended to be TRUE. 
modificationDate timestamp without time zone  
name varchar(255) The name of the supplier as used. 
supplierName varchar(50) UNIQUE The name of the supplier as used by the supplier, i.e. at interfaces. 
supportsReservation boolean NOT_NULL Whether the supplier supports reservations. Recommended to be FALSE.
Note that IOM currently does not supports reservations at this point. 
supportsResponse boolean NOT_NULL Whether the supplier supports order responses.
If FALSE, the data determined by the DOSE process (INITIAL-response) are assumed immediately. Otherwise IOM is waiting for a response message from the supplier. 
singlePositionArticle boolean Whether the supplier can handle only one position per product.
If TRUE, the IOM will merge positions with the same product to one position and sums up their quantities (for the order placement message to the supplier). 
internalSupplierName varchar(50) UNIQUE, NOT_NULL The name of the supplier as used by the IOM.
Note that spaces are not allowed and lowercase is recommended. 
SupplierDO parentSupplierRef bigint The parent supplier instance.
Supplier inheritance is only used for users and roles assignments. Roles granted in a parent supplier are also available in all descendant suppliers. 
cleanParentOnImport boolean NOT_NULL false After a product import,
whether information given from the supplier (manufacturerArticleNo and EAN) should be set to NULL at master products (master variations). 
ignoreAdditionalPositions boolean NOT_NULL false Specifies the handling of additional order positions in messages by the supplier.
If TRUE, the IOM ignores additional positions.
If FALSE, the IOM throws an InvalidReferenceException in case of an additional order position. 
businessObjectProcessingDelay varchar(50) Delay of message processing, which enables the cancellation of business messages like dispatches etc. before the processing has begun.
Example for duration in minutes = m (e.g., 30m), example for duration in hours = h (e.g., 1h).
Note that this functionality currently is only used for messages from the OMT.
 
SupplierTypeDefDO supplierTypeDefRef integer NOT_NULL 1 The type of the supplier. I.e. retailer, warehouse or drop shipment.

Such "missing" foreign keys are denoted with [[ ]].

[2] Constraints:
PK : the column is part of the primary key
UNIQUE: does don't cover unique constraints and indexes defined on more than one column.
